    <p>Fam­ily Ro­mance, LLC (2019, PG13)</p>
    <p>In this work by Os­car-nom­i­nated direc­tor Werner Herzog, love is a busi­ness at Ja­panese agency Fam­ily Ro­mance, which of­fers a sub­sti­tute rental ser­vice. A man is hired to im­per­son­ate the miss­ing fa­ther of a 12-year-old girl.</p>
    <p>PRICE: $10 for a 48-hour rental pe­riod INFO: str.sg/Jeeo</p>
    <p>Jojo Rab­bit (2019, PG13)</p>
    <p>The film fol­lows a lonely Ger­man boy, Jojo, whose world­view is turned up­side-down when he dis­cov­ers his mother is hid­ing a young Jewish girl in their at­tic. Aided only by his imag­i­nary friend, Adolf Hitler, Jojo must con­front his blind na­tion­al­ism. Win­ner of Best Adapted Screen­play at this year’s Os­cars.</p>
    <p>WHERE: The Pro­jec­tor, Level 5 Golden Mile Tower, 6001 Beach Road</p>
    <p>MRT: Ni­coll High­way WHEN: Wed, 5pm AD­MIS­SION: $13.50 INFO: str.sg/J6k9</p>


